## SDK Primitives Overview

The `nen` SDK provides these main primitives:

| Primitive | Purpose | Uses VLM | When to Use |
|-----------|---------|----------|-------------|
| `agent.execute()` | Execute natural language action | Yes | Complex UI interactions, dynamic content |
| `agent.verify()` | Check UI state | Yes | Verify page loaded, confirm success |
| `agent.extract()` | Extract structured data | Yes | Read tables, forms, lists |
| `computer.click_at/move/scroll` | Direct mouse control | No | Known coordinates, precise clicks |
| `computer.type/press/hotkey` | Direct keyboard control | No | Type text, press keys, shortcuts |

**Decision Tree for Choosing Primitives:**

```
Need to interact with UI?
├─ Know exact coordinates? → Use computer.click_at()/computer.hotkey()/computer.press()
├─ Need to find element visually? → Use agent.execute()
├─ Just checking state? → Use agent.verify()
└─ Need to extract data? → Use agent.extract()
```

