## Computer Control

### Overview

The `Computer` class provides **deterministic** (non-VLM) keyboard and mouse control. Use when you know exact key sequences or coordinates.

```python
computer = Computer()
computer.click_at(500, 300)
computer.type("hello@example.com")
computer.press("Return")
```

### Keyboard

```python
# Type text
computer.type("hello@example.com")
computer.type("password", interval=0.01)  # slower typing

# Press single key
computer.press("Return")
computer.press("Tab")
computer.press("Escape")
computer.press("BackSpace")

# Keyboard shortcuts (Linux key names!)
computer.hotkey("ctrl", "a")          # select all
computer.hotkey("ctrl", "c")          # copy
computer.hotkey("ctrl", "v")          # paste
computer.hotkey("ctrl", "shift", "s") # save as
```

### Mouse

```python
# Left click
computer.click_at(100, 200)

# Right click
computer.click_at(100, 200, button="right")

# Move cursor
computer.move(500, 300)

# Scroll
computer.scroll("down", 3)
computer.scroll("up", 5)
computer.scroll("down", 3, x=400, y=300)  # scroll at position
```

